at|mitche:  Bidding:   Let's review what the NT bidder's response to a Jacoby transfer of 2@h should be. 
Opener looks at her spade suit.  If she has 2 or 3 spades, she bids 2@s.  
If she has 4 spades, she may SuperAccept,
if you use them. (I think you should.) But the first bid is to accept the transfer. This is not optional.  
So our auction should go 1NT, 2@h 2@s 3NT.  Then opener has to look at the rest of her hand.   
With 3 spades and a ruffing value, i.e. a doubleton, opener bids 4@s.
If opener is 3334, she looks at her honors. |
